<h2>5.3 Models &mdash; the database entities</h2>
<p>The Models folder contains one C# class per database table (generated by EF Core's database-first
scaffolding). The most important is <code>Donor</code>. Note the special <code>Age</code> property: the table has no age
column, so age is calculated from <code>DateOfBirth</code> and marked <code>[NotMapped]</code> so EF does not look for a column.</p>
<h3>Models/Donor.cs</h3>
<pre>using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.Schema;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Models;

public partial class Donor
{
    public uint Id { get; set; }

    // The table has no age column, so derive it from date_of_birth. [NotMapped] stops EF
    // from looking for a column.
    [NotMapped]
    public int Age
    {
        get
        {
            var today = DateOnly.FromDateTime(DateTime.Today);
            var years = today.Year - DateOfBirth.Year;
            if (DateOfBirth &gt; today.AddYears(-years)) years--;
            return years &lt; 0 ? 0 : years;
        }
    }

    public string FirstName { get; set; } = null!;
    public string LastName { get; set; } = null!;
    public byte BloodGroupId { get; set; }
    public string Gender { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateOnly DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    public string Phone { get; set; } = null!;
    public string Email { get; set; } = null!;
    public string Address { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateOnly RegistrationDate { get; set; }
    public DateOnly? LastDonationDate { get; set; }
    public string? EligibilityStatus { get; set; }
    public DateTime? CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? UpdatedAt { get; set; }

    // Navigation properties: the linked blood group and this donor's donations.
    public virtual BloodGroup BloodGroup { get; set; } = null!;
    public virtual ICollection&lt;Donation&gt; Donations { get; set; } = new List&lt;Donation&gt;();
}</pre>

<h3>Related entities (referenced by the donor code)</h3>
<p><code>BloodGroup</code> stores the group <code>Code</code> (e.g. &ldquo;A+&rdquo;). <code>Donation</code> and <code>BloodScreening</code> matter for deletion,
because a donor may be referenced by donation rows, which are in turn referenced by screening rows.</p>
<pre>// Models/BloodGroup.cs (key fields)
public partial class BloodGroup
{
    public byte Id { get; set; }
    public string Code { get; set; } = null!;   // "A+", "O-", ...
    // navigation collections: Donors, Donations, BloodRequests, Patients, BloodInventory
}

// Models/Donation.cs (key fields)
public partial class Donation
{
    public uint Id { get; set; }
    public uint DonorId { get; set; }           // links back to a Donor
    public byte BloodGroupId { get; set; }
    // ... units, dates, statuses ...
    public virtual BloodScreening? BloodScreening { get; set; }
}

// Models/BloodScreening.cs (key fields)
public partial class BloodScreening
{
    public uint Id { get; set; }
    public uint DonationId { get; set; }         // links back to a Donation
    // ... HIV/HepB/HepC/Syphilis statuses, notes, date ...
}</pre>

<h3>Other scaffolded entities</h3>
<p>The remaining model classes are standard EF entities that map one-to-one to their tables. They are not
used directly by the donor feature but complete the schema:</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Entity</th><th>Table</th><th>Represents</th></tr>
<tr><td>Admin</td><td>admins</td><td>Administrative user accounts.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AuditLog</td><td>audit_logs</td><td>A database-side audit table (separate from the in-memory ledger).</td></tr>
<tr><td>BloodInventory</td><td>blood_inventory</td><td>Units available per blood group.</td></tr>
<tr><td>BloodRequest</td><td>blood_requests</td><td>Requests for blood from patients.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hospital</td><td>hospitals</td><td>Hospitals in the network.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Patient</td><td>patients</td><td>Patients linked to hospitals and blood groups.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Models/BloodBankMsContext.cs &mdash; the DbContext</h3>
<p>The <code>DbContext</code> is EF Core's gateway to the database. It exposes each table as a <code>DbSet&lt;T&gt;</code> and, in
<code>OnModelCreating</code>, describes how each entity maps to columns, keys, indexes and relationships. The mapping
code is long and auto-generated; the essential parts are the DbSets and (as an example) the Donor mapping:</p>
<pre>public partial class BloodBankMsContext : DbContext
{
    public BloodBankMsContext(DbContextOptions&lt;BloodBankMsContext&gt; options) : base(options) { }

    public virtual DbSet&lt;Admin&gt; Admins { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;AuditLog&gt; AuditLogs { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;BloodGroup&gt; BloodGroups { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;BloodInventory&gt; BloodInventories { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;BloodRequest&gt; BloodRequests { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;BloodScreening&gt; BloodScreenings { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;Donation&gt; Donations { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;Donor&gt; Donors { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;Hospital&gt; Hospitals { get; set; }
    public virtual DbSet&lt;Patient&gt; Patients { get; set; }

    // Connection is configured in Program.cs via AddDbContext, so nothing to do here.
    protected override void OnConfiguring(DbContextOptionsBuilder optionsBuilder) { }

    protected override void OnModelCreating(ModelBuilder modelBuilder)
    {
        // ... one entity() block per table. Example for Donor: ...
        modelBuilder.Entity&lt;Donor&gt;(entity =&gt;
        {
            entity.HasKey(e =&gt; e.Id).HasName("PRIMARY");
            entity.ToTable("donors");
            entity.Property(e =&gt; e.FirstName).HasColumnName("first_name");
            entity.Property(e =&gt; e.BloodGroupId).HasColumnName("blood_group_id");
            // ... every other column mapped to its snake_case name ...
            entity.HasOne(d =&gt; d.BloodGroup).WithMany(p =&gt; p.Donors)
                .HasForeignKey(d =&gt; d.BloodGroupId)
                .HasConstraintName("fk_donors_blood_groups");
        });
        // ... blocks for Admin, Donation, BloodScreening, Patient, etc. ...
    }
}</pre>

<h2>5.4 DTOs &mdash; the data contract</h2>
<p>DTOs (Data Transfer Objects) define the exact JSON exchanged with the frontend, kept separate from the
database entities.</p>
<h3>Dtos/DonorFormInput.cs</h3>
<pre>namespace BloodBankAPI.Dtos;

// This is the exact shape the React form sends up as JSON. It is deliberately kept separate
// from the EF Core "Donor" entity so the frontend can speak in simple values (a blood-group
// code like "A+", age as plain text) while the entity/database keep their own structure.
public class DonorFormInput
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string FirstName { get; set; } = "";
    public string LastName { get; set; } = "";

    // Age is a string (not an int) because the number &lt;input&gt; can arrive empty, and there is
    // no age column in the database - the server converts it into a date_of_birth.
    public string? Age { get; set; }

    public string Gender { get; set; } = "Male";
    public string Phone { get; set; } = "";
    public string Email { get; set; } = "";
    public string BloodGroup { get; set; } = "A+";
    public string EligibilityStatus { get; set; } = "Eligible";
}</pre>
<h3>Dtos/AuditLogEntry.cs</h3>
<pre>using System;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Dtos;

// A single line in the in-memory audit / cash-flow ledger that the "Ledger & Cash Flow"
// tab displays. This is not a database table - see AuditLedger for where it lives.
public class AuditLogEntry
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public DateTime Timestamp { get; set; }
    public string Operation { get; set; } = "";
    public string Details { get; set; } = "";
    public decimal CashFlowAmount { get; set; }
    public string LogType { get; set; } = "System";
}</pre>

<h2>5.5 Services &mdash; shared logic</h2>
<p>The Services folder holds logic reused by more than one controller, so it is written once.</p>

<h3>Services/AuditLedger.cs</h3>
<p>A thread-safe, in-memory list of ledger entries shared by all controllers. It resets when the API
restarts. <code>Record</code> appends a line; <code>Snapshot</code> returns a copy newest-first.</p>
<pre>using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using BloodBankAPI.Dtos;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Services;

public static class AuditLedger
{
    private static readonly List&lt;AuditLogEntry&gt; _logs = new()
    {
        new AuditLogEntry { Id = 1, Timestamp = DateTime.Now.AddDays(-1), Operation = "SYSTEM COLD BOOT", Details = "Data synchronization pipeline established with local MySQL instance.", CashFlowAmount = 0.00m, LogType = "System" },
        new AuditLogEntry { Id = 2, Timestamp = DateTime.Now.AddHours(-4), Operation = "GOVERNMENT GRANT", Details = "Administrative overhead subsidy allocation received.", CashFlowAmount = 25000.00m, LogType = "Financial" }
    };

    // Return a copy of the ledger, newest entries first.
    public static List&lt;AuditLogEntry&gt; Snapshot()
    {
        lock (_logs)
        {
            return _logs.OrderByDescending(l =&gt; l.Timestamp).ToList();
        }
    }

    // Append a new line, giving it the next id automatically. The lock keeps concurrent
    // requests from corrupting the list.
    public static void Record(string operation, string details, decimal cashFlowAmount, string logType)
    {
        lock (_logs)
        {
            _logs.Add(new AuditLogEntry
            {
                Id = _logs.Any() ? _logs.Max(l =&gt; l.Id) + 1 : 1,
                Timestamp = DateTime.Now,
                Operation = operation,
                Details = details,
                CashFlowAmount = cashFlowAmount,
                LogType = logType
            });
        }
    }
}</pre>

<h3>Services/DonorMapper.cs</h3>
<p>Converts a <code>Donor</code> entity into the flat object the frontend expects &mdash; blood group as its code string,
plus the computed age &mdash; so every controller returns donors in the same shape.</p>
<pre>using BloodBankAPI.Models;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Services;

public static class DonorMapper
{
    public static object ToApiShape(Donor d) =&gt; new
    {
        id = d.Id,
        firstName = d.FirstName,
        lastName = d.LastName,
        age = d.Age,
        gender = d.Gender,
        phone = d.Phone,
        email = d.Email,
        bloodGroup = d.BloodGroup != null ? d.BloodGroup.Code : null,
        eligibilityStatus = d.EligibilityStatus
    };
}</pre>

<h3>Services/DonorWriteHelpers.cs</h3>
<p>Shared write logic used by both the create and update controllers: find the blood-group id from a code,
copy editable fields from the form, and translate an age string into a birth date.</p>
<pre>using System;
using System.Linq;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using BloodBankAPI.Dtos;
using BloodBankAPI.Models;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Services;

public static class DonorWriteHelpers
{
    // Look up the blood_groups row whose code matches the requested value (e.g. "A+") and
    // return its id. Falls back to the first group if nothing matches.
    public static async Task&lt;byte&gt; ResolveBloodGroupIdAsync(BloodBankMsContext context, string bloodGroupCode)
    {
        var groups = await context.Set&lt;BloodGroup&gt;().ToListAsync();

        var match = groups.FirstOrDefault(g =&gt;
            g.Code != null && g.Code.Equals(bloodGroupCode, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));

        if (match != null) return match.Id;
        return groups.FirstOrDefault()?.Id ?? (byte)1;
    }

    // Copy the editable text fields from the form onto the entity.
    public static void ApplyEditableFields(Donor donor, DonorFormInput input)
    {
        donor.FirstName = input.FirstName;
        donor.LastName = input.LastName;
        donor.Gender = input.Gender;
        donor.Phone = input.Phone;
        donor.Email = input.Email;
        donor.EligibilityStatus = input.EligibilityStatus;
    }

    // There is no age column, so translate the entered age into a date_of_birth. Invalid or
    // empty values are simply ignored (the existing birth date is left untouched).
    public static void ApplyAgeAsBirthDate(Donor donor, string? age)
    {
        if (int.TryParse(age, out var years) && years &gt; 0 && years &lt; 120)
        {
            donor.DateOfBirth = DateOnly.FromDateTime(DateTime.Today.AddYears(-years));
        }
    }
}</pre>

<h2>5.6 Controllers &mdash; the HTTP endpoints (one per CRUD action)</h2>

<h3>Controllers/DonorsReadController.cs (Read)</h3>
<p>Owns every GET: list all donors, search by blood group, and read the audit trail. It loads the blood
group with <code>.Include(...)</code> so the response can include the group code.</p>
<pre>using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using BloodBankAPI.Dtos;
using BloodBankAPI.Models;
using BloodBankAPI.Services;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Controllers;

[ApiController]
[Route("api/donors")]
public class DonorsReadController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly BloodBankMsContext _context;
    public DonorsReadController(BloodBankMsContext context) { _context = context; }

    // GET: api/donors  ->  return every donor
    [HttpGet]
    public async Task&lt;ActionResult&gt; GetDonors()
    {
        try
        {
            var donors = await _context.Set&lt;Donor&gt;()
                .Include(d =&gt; d.BloodGroup)
                .ToListAsync();
            return Ok(donors.Select(DonorMapper.ToApiShape));
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            var detail = ex.InnerException?.Message ?? ex.Message;
            return StatusCode(500, $"Internal directory query failed: {detail}");
        }
    }

    // GET: api/donors/search?bloodGroup=A+  ->  donors filtered by blood group
    [HttpGet("search")]
    public async Task&lt;ActionResult&gt; SearchByBloodGroup([FromQuery] string bloodGroup)
    {
        try
        {
            var donors = await _context.Set&lt;Donor&gt;().Include(d =&gt; d.BloodGroup).ToListAsync();

            if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(bloodGroup))
            {
                donors = donors
                    .Where(d =&gt; d.BloodGroup != null
                        && !string.IsNullOrEmpty(d.BloodGroup.Code)
                        && d.BloodGroup.Code.Equals(bloodGroup, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
                    .ToList();
            }
            return Ok(donors.Select(DonorMapper.ToApiShape));
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            var detail = ex.InnerException?.Message ?? ex.Message;
            return StatusCode(500, $"Directory search failed: {detail}");
        }
    }

    // GET: api/donors/audit-trail  ->  the in-memory cash-flow ledger
    [HttpGet("audit-trail")]
    public ActionResult&lt;IEnumerable&lt;AuditLogEntry&gt;&gt; GetAuditTrail()
    {
        return Ok(AuditLedger.Snapshot());
    }
}</pre>

<h3>Controllers/DonorCreateController.cs (Create)</h3>
<p>Handles <code>POST /donors</code>. Builds a new entity, fills required columns, resolves the blood group, stores the
age as a birth date, saves, and records the action in the ledger.</p>
<pre>using System;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;
using BloodBankAPI.Dtos;
using BloodBankAPI.Models;
using BloodBankAPI.Services;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Controllers;

[ApiController]
[Route("api/donors")]
public class DonorCreateController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly BloodBankMsContext _context;
    public DonorCreateController(BloodBankMsContext context) { _context = context; }

    // POST: api/donors  ->  insert a new donor row
    [HttpPost]
    public async Task&lt;ActionResult&gt; AddDonor([FromBody] DonorFormInput input)
    {
        try
        {
            var donor = new Donor
            {
                Address = "Islamabad",                                   // address is NOT NULL in the DB
                DateOfBirth = new DateOnly(2000, 1, 1),                  // placeholder, replaced by the age below
                RegistrationDate = DateOnly.FromDateTime(DateTime.Today),
                BloodGroupId = await DonorWriteHelpers.ResolveBloodGroupIdAsync(_context, input.BloodGroup)
            };

            DonorWriteHelpers.ApplyEditableFields(donor, input);
            DonorWriteHelpers.ApplyAgeAsBirthDate(donor, input.Age);

            _context.Set&lt;Donor&gt;().Add(donor);
            await _context.SaveChangesAsync();

            AuditLedger.Record(
                "DONOR REGISTRATION",
                $"Successfully onboarded donor profile: {input.FirstName} {input.LastName}.",
                1500.00m,
                "Financial");

            return Ok(DonorMapper.ToApiShape(donor));
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            var detail = ex.InnerException?.Message ?? ex.Message;
            return StatusCode(500, $"Database injection rejected transaction: {detail}");
        }
    }
}</pre>

<h3>Controllers/DonorUpdateController.cs (Update)</h3>
<p>Handles <code>PUT /donors/{id}</code>. Finds the existing donor (casting the id to <code>uint</code> to match the key type),
applies the edits, saves, and logs a &ldquo;PROFILE MODIFICATION&rdquo; entry.</p>
<pre>using System;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;
using BloodBankAPI.Dtos;
using BloodBankAPI.Models;
using BloodBankAPI.Services;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Controllers;

[ApiController]
[Route("api/donors")]
public class DonorUpdateController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly BloodBankMsContext _context;
    public DonorUpdateController(BloodBankMsContext context) { _context = context; }

    // PUT: api/donors/{id}  ->  update the donor with this id
    [HttpPut("{id}")]
    public async Task&lt;IActionResult&gt; UpdateDonor(int id, [FromBody] DonorFormInput input)
    {
        // The id in the URL must match the id in the body, otherwise we'd edit the wrong row.
        if (id != input.Id) return BadRequest("Target identifier tracking mismatch.");

        // Donor.Id is a uint. FindAsync won't coerce an int, so cast it or it throws.
        var donor = await _context.Set&lt;Donor&gt;().FindAsync((uint)id);
        if (donor == null) return NotFound();

        try
        {
            DonorWriteHelpers.ApplyEditableFields(donor, input);
            donor.BloodGroupId = await DonorWriteHelpers.ResolveBloodGroupIdAsync(_context, input.BloodGroup);
            DonorWriteHelpers.ApplyAgeAsBirthDate(donor, input.Age);

            // The entity is already tracked (we fetched it with FindAsync), so saving persists
            // the changes - no need to force EntityState.Modified.
            await _context.SaveChangesAsync();

            AuditLedger.Record(
                "PROFILE MODIFICATION",
                $"Administrative revision applied to Donor Tracking Index #{id}.",
                0.00m,
                "System");

            return NoContent();
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            return StatusCode(500, $"Target patch modification failed: {ex.Message}");
        }
    }
}</pre>

<h3>Controllers/DonorDeleteController.cs (Delete)</h3>
<p>Handles <code>DELETE /donors/{id}</code>. It tries a straight delete; if the database blocks it because the donor is
referenced by donation rows, it removes those dependent rows (and their screenings) first, then retries.</p>
<pre>using System;
using System.Linq;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using BloodBankAPI.Models;
using BloodBankAPI.Services;

namespace BloodBankAPI.Controllers;

[ApiController]
[Route("api/donors")]
public class DonorDeleteController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly BloodBankMsContext _context;
    public DonorDeleteController(BloodBankMsContext context) { _context = context; }

    // DELETE: api/donors/{id}  ->  delete this donor (and its dependent rows if required)
    [HttpDelete("{id}")]
    public async Task&lt;IActionResult&gt; DeleteDonor(int id)
    {
        var donor = await _context.Set&lt;Donor&gt;().FindAsync((uint)id);
        if (donor == null) return NotFound();

        try
        {
            var savedName = $"{donor.FirstName} {donor.LastName}";

            try
            {
                // Happy path: no related rows, so the donor deletes straight away.
                _context.Set&lt;Donor&gt;().Remove(donor);
                await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
            }
            catch (DbUpdateException)
            {
                // The donor is referenced by donation rows, so MySQL rejected the delete.
                // Remove the dependent rows first, then delete the donor.
                var linkedDonations = await _context.Set&lt;Donation&gt;()
                    .Where(d =&gt; d.DonorId == donor.Id)
                    .ToListAsync();

                if (linkedDonations.Count &gt; 0)
                {
                    var donationIds = linkedDonations.Select(d =&gt; d.Id).ToList();
                    var linkedScreenings = await _context.Set&lt;BloodScreening&gt;()
                        .Where(s =&gt; donationIds.Contains(s.DonationId))
                        .ToListAsync();

                    _context.Set&lt;BloodScreening&gt;().RemoveRange(linkedScreenings);
                    _context.Set&lt;Donation&gt;().RemoveRange(linkedDonations);
                }

                _context.Set&lt;Donor&gt;().Remove(donor);
                await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
            }

            AuditLedger.Record(
                "RECORD PURGE",
                $"Permanently dropped file indexing for donor: {savedName}.",
                -450.00m,
                "Financial");

            return NoContent();
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            return StatusCode(500, $"Purge tracking operations aborted: {ex.Message}");
        }
    }
}</pre>

<!-- ============================ CHAPTER 6 ============================ -->
<h1 class="pagebreak">Chapter 6 &mdash; Frontend Code Walkthrough</h1>
<p class="chapter-intro">This chapter presents every frontend file with its full source and an explanation. App.jsx holds the logic; the components render it.</p>

<h2>6.1 main.jsx &mdash; the entry point</h2>
<p>Vite loads this first. It mounts the <code>&lt;App /&gt;</code> component into the page's root element.</p>
<pre>import { StrictMode } from 'react'
import { createRoot } from 'react-dom/client'
import App from './App.jsx'
import './App.css'

createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(
  &lt;StrictMode&gt;
    &lt;App /&gt;
  &lt;/StrictMode&gt;,
)</pre>

<h2>6.2 services/api.js &mdash; the API client</h2>
<p>A single Axios instance every request goes through. The base URL points at the API; the response
interceptor attaches a readable <code>friendlyMessage</code> so the UI can tell &ldquo;server error&rdquo; from &ldquo;server unreachable&rdquo;.</p>
<pre>import axios from 'axios';

const API = axios.create({
  baseURL: 'http://localhost:5236/api', // http, port 5236 - matches the API's launch profile
  timeout: 15000,
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
});

// Attach a readable failure reason so the UI can tell "server error" from "server unreachable".
API.interceptors.response.use(
  (response) =&gt; response,
  (error) =&gt; {
    if (error.response) {
      const body = error.response.data;
      error.friendlyMessage = `Server error ${error.response.status}: ` +
        (typeof body === 'string' ? body : JSON.stringify(body));
    } else if (error.request) {
      error.friendlyMessage =
        `No response from API at ${API.defaults.baseURL}. ` +
        `Is the backend running (dotnet run) and is MySQL up?`;
    } else {
      error.friendlyMessage = error.message;
    }
    console.error('[API ERROR]', error.friendlyMessage, error);
    return Promise.reject(error);
  }
);

export default API;</pre>

<h2>6.3 App.jsx &mdash; the container</h2>
<p>This is the heart of the frontend. It owns all state (donor list, form, theme, auth, ledger) and all the
functions that call the API, then hands data and callbacks to the presentational components.</p>
<pre>import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import API from './services/api';
import './index.css';

import LoginScreen from './components/LoginScreen';
import Sidebar from './components/Sidebar';
import TopHeader from './components/TopHeader';
import DonorsTab from './components/DonorsTab';
import StatsTab from './components/StatsTab';
import LedgerTab from './components/LedgerTab';
import SettingsTab from './components/SettingsTab';
import DonorModal from './components/DonorModal';
import Footer from './components/Footer';

function App() {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState('light');
  const [sidebarCollapsed, setSidebarCollapsed] = useState(false);

  // Auth
  const [isLoggedIn, setIsLoggedIn] = useState(false);
  const [username, setUsername] = useState('');
  const [password, setPassword] = useState('');
  const [loginError, setLoginError] = useState('');

  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState('donors');

  // Donor directory
  const [donors, setDonors] = useState([]);
  const [selectedGroup, setSelectedGroup] = useState('');
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState('');
  const [hasSearched, setHasSearched] = useState(false);

  // Audit ledger
  const [auditLogs, setAuditLogs] = useState([]);
  const [auditLoading, setAuditLoading] = useState(false);

  const quotes = [ /* rotating login-screen quotes */ ];
  const [currentQuoteIndex, setCurrentQuoteIndex] = useState(0);

  // Add/edit modal
  const [isModalOpen, setIsModalOpen] = useState(false);
  const [formMode, setFormMode] = useState('add');
  const [formData, setFormData] = useState({
    id: 0, firstName: '', lastName: '', age: '', gender: 'Male', phone: '', email: '', bloodGroup: 'A+', eligibilityStatus: 'Eligible'
  });

  const bloodGroups = ['A+', 'A-', 'B+', 'B-', 'AB+', 'AB-', 'O+', 'O-'];
  const [isHovered, setIsHovered] = useState(false);

  // Cycle the login-screen quote every couple of minutes
  useEffect(() =&gt; {
    const quoteInterval = setInterval(() =&gt; {
      setCurrentQuoteIndex((prevIndex) =&gt; (prevIndex + 1) % quotes.length);
    }, 120000);
    return () =&gt; clearInterval(quoteInterval);
  }, []);

  const handleLogin = (e) =&gt; {
    e.preventDefault();
    if (username === 'admin' && password === 'ghost230') {
      setIsLoggedIn(true);
      setLoginError('');
    } else {
      setLoginError('Invalid administrative credentials.');
    }
  };

  // Load donors - either all of them or filtered by the selected blood group.
  const handleSearch = async (e) =&gt; {
    if (e) e.preventDefault();
    setLoading(true); setError(''); setHasSearched(true);
    try {
      let response;
      if (selectedGroup) {
        response = await API.get(`/donors/search?bloodGroup=${encodeURIComponent(selectedGroup)}`);
      } else {
        response = await API.get('/donors');
      }
      setDonors(response.data);
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err.friendlyMessage || 'Could not fetch synchronized directory lines.');
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  const fetchAuditTrail = async () =&gt; {
    setAuditLoading(true);
    try {
      const response = await API.get('/donors/audit-trail');
      setAuditLogs(response.data);
    } catch (err) {
      console.error(err);
    } finally {
      setAuditLoading(false);
    }
  };

  // On login, pull the initial data.
  useEffect(() =&gt; {
    if (isLoggedIn) { handleSearch(); fetchAuditTrail(); }
  }, [isLoggedIn]);

  const openAddModal = () =&gt; {
    setFormMode('add');
    setFormData({ id: 0, firstName: '', lastName: '', age: '', gender: 'Male', phone: '', email: '', bloodGroup: selectedGroup || 'A+', eligibilityStatus: 'Eligible' });
    setIsModalOpen(true);
  };

  const openEditModal = (donor) =&gt; {
    setFormMode('edit');
    const groupText = donor.bloodGroup && typeof donor.bloodGroup === 'object' ? donor.bloodGroup.name || donor.bloodGroup.type || 'A+' : donor.bloodGroup || 'A+';
    // age is sent to the API as a string, so coerce it here
    setFormData({ ...donor, age: donor.age != null ? String(donor.age) : '', bloodGroup: groupText });
    setIsModalOpen(true);
  };

  // Create (add) or update (edit), then refetch so the table + ledger stay in sync.
  const handleFormSubmit = async (e) =&gt; {
    e.preventDefault();
    try {
      if (formMode === 'add') { await API.post('/donors', formData); }
      else { await API.put(`/donors/${formData.id}`, formData); }
      setIsModalOpen(false); handleSearch(); fetchAuditTrail();
    } catch (err) {
      alert(err.friendlyMessage || 'Error committing transactional schema changes.');
    }
  };

  const handleDeleteDonor = async (id) =&gt; {
    if (window.confirm('Are you certain you wish to purge this record index completely?')) {
      try {
        await API.delete(`/donors/${id}`);
        handleSearch(); fetchAuditTrail();
      } catch (err) {
        alert(err.friendlyMessage || 'Failed to drop data index.');
      }
    }
  };

  // Logged-out view
  if (!isLoggedIn) {
    return (
      &lt;LoginScreen
        theme={theme}
        username={username} setUsername={setUsername}
        password={password} setPassword={setPassword}
        loginError={loginError} handleLogin={handleLogin}
        quotes={quotes} currentQuoteIndex={currentQuoteIndex}
        isHovered={isHovered} setIsHovered={setIsHovered}
      /&gt;
    );
  }

  // Logged-in workspace
  return (
    &lt;div className={`theme-wrapper ${theme}`}&gt;
      &lt;div className={`app-workspace-layout ${sidebarCollapsed ? 'sidebar-collapsed' : ''}`}&gt;
        &lt;Sidebar activeTab={activeTab} setActiveTab={setActiveTab}
          onLogout={() =&gt; { setIsLoggedIn(false); setHasSearched(false); }} /&gt;
        &lt;div className="app-content-viewport"&gt;
          &lt;TopHeader activeTab={activeTab} sidebarCollapsed={sidebarCollapsed}
            setSidebarCollapsed={setSidebarCollapsed} onAddDonor={openAddModal} /&gt;
          {activeTab === 'donors' && (
            &lt;DonorsTab selectedGroup={selectedGroup} setSelectedGroup={setSelectedGroup}
              handleSearch={handleSearch} bloodGroups={bloodGroups}
              hasSearched={hasSearched} error={error} loading={loading}
              donors={donors} openEditModal={openEditModal} handleDeleteDonor={handleDeleteDonor} /&gt;
          )}
          {activeTab === 'stats' && &lt;StatsTab donors={donors} bloodGroups={bloodGroups} /&gt;}
          {activeTab === 'audit' && &lt;LedgerTab auditLogs={auditLogs} auditLoading={auditLoading} /&gt;}
          {activeTab === 'settings' && &lt;SettingsTab theme={theme} setTheme={setTheme} /&gt;}
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;Footer /&gt;
      {isModalOpen && (
        &lt;DonorModal formMode={formMode} formData={formData} setFormData={setFormData}
          bloodGroups={bloodGroups} onClose={() =&gt; setIsModalOpen(false)} onSubmit={handleFormSubmit} /&gt;
      )}
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
}

export default App;</pre>

<h2>6.4 components/ &mdash; the UI pieces</h2>

<h3>components/WaveCanvas.jsx</h3>
<p>A self-contained animated background (sine waves + floating particles) for the login screen. It manages
its own canvas and animation loop; the parent only passes <code>isHovered</code> to speed it up and shift the colour.</p>
<pre>import { useRef, useEffect } from 'react';

function WaveCanvas({ isHovered }) {
  const canvasRef = useRef(null);

  useEffect(() =&gt; {
    if (!canvasRef.current) return;
    const canvas = canvasRef.current;
    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
    let animationId;

    const resizeCanvas = () =&gt; {
      canvas.width = window.innerWidth;
      canvas.height = window.innerHeight;
    };
    resizeCanvas();
    window.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);

    let phase = 0;
    const baseSpeed = 0.003, hoverSpeed = 0.005;
    let currentSpeed = baseSpeed;

    // Floating background particles
    const particles = [];
    for (let i = 0; i &lt; 45; i++) {
      particles.push({
        x: Math.random() * window.innerWidth,
        y: Math.random() * window.innerHeight,
        size: Math.random() * 2 + 0.5,
        speedX: Math.random() * 0.4 - 0.2,
        speedY: Math.random() * -0.5 - 0.1,
        alpha: Math.random() * 0.5 + 0.2
      });
    }

    const render = () =&gt; {
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
      const targetSpeed = isHovered ? hoverSpeed : baseSpeed;
      currentSpeed += (targetSpeed - currentSpeed) * 0.1;
      phase += currentSpeed;

      particles.forEach(p =&gt; {
        p.x += p.speedX * (isHovered ? 2 : 1);
        p.y += p.speedY * (isHovered ? 1.8 : 1);
        if (p.y &lt; 0) { p.y = canvas.height; p.x = Math.random() * canvas.width; }
        if (p.x &lt; 0 || p.x &gt; canvas.width) p.x = Math.random() * canvas.width;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(p.x, p.y, p.size, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(${isHovered ? '255, 0, 85' : '225, 29, 72'}, ${p.alpha})`;
        ctx.shadowBlur = isHovered ? 8 : 2;
        ctx.shadowColor = 'rgba(255, 0, 85, 0.5)';
        ctx.fill();
      });

      // Draw several overlapping sine waves
      const waveLayers = [
        { amplitude: 45, frequency: 0.002,  alpha: 0.18, offset: 0 },
        { amplitude: 30, frequency: 0.0035, alpha: 0.12, offset: Math.PI / 3 },
        { amplitude: 60, frequency: 0.0015, alpha: 0.08, offset: Math.PI / 1.5 },
        { amplitude: 20, frequency: 0.005,  alpha: 0.15, offset: Math.PI / 2 }
      ];
      waveLayers.forEach((layer, i) =&gt; {
        ctx.beginPath();
        const colorGlow = isHovered ? `rgba(255, 0, 85, ${layer.alpha + 0.4})` : `rgba(2, 132, 199, ${layer.alpha})`;
        ctx.strokeStyle = colorGlow;
        ctx.lineWidth = i === 0 ? 3 : 1.5;
        ctx.shadowBlur = isHovered ? 50 : 10;
        ctx.shadowColor = isHovered ? 'rgba(255, 0, 85, 0.8)' : 'rgba(2, 132, 199, 0.4)';
        for (let x = 0; x &lt;= canvas.width; x += 10) {
          const y = canvas.height / 2 +
            Math.sin(x * layer.frequency + phase + layer.offset) * layer.amplitude +
            Math.cos(x * 0.001 - phase * 0.5) * 20;
          if (x === 0) ctx.moveTo(x, y); else ctx.lineTo(x, y);
        }
        ctx.stroke();
      });
      ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
      animationId = requestAnimationFrame(render);
    };

    render();
    return () =&gt; {
      cancelAnimationFrame(animationId);
      window.removeEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);
    };
  }, [isHovered]);

  return &lt;canvas ref={canvasRef} className="ps3-wave-canvas-substrate" /&gt;;
}

export default WaveCanvas;</pre>

<h3>components/LoginScreen.jsx</h3>
<p>The logged-out view: the animated background plus the sign-in card. It renders auth state passed from App
and reports events back through setter/handler props.</p>
<pre>import WaveCanvas from './WaveCanvas';

function LoginScreen({ theme, username, setUsername, password, setPassword,
  loginError, handleLogin, quotes, currentQuoteIndex, isHovered, setIsHovered }) {
  return (
    &lt;div className={`theme-wrapper ${theme}`}&gt;
      &lt;div className="login-wrapper"&gt;
        &lt;WaveCanvas isHovered={isHovered} /&gt;
        &lt;div className="login-glow-box"
          onMouseEnter={() =&gt; setIsHovered(true)}
          onMouseLeave={() =&gt; setIsHovered(false)}&gt;
          &lt;div className="login-card"&gt;
            &lt;h2&gt;BLOOD BANK PORTAL&lt;/h2&gt;
            &lt;p className="login-subtitle"&gt;AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;div className="login-quote-box animate-fade-in" key={currentQuoteIndex}&gt;
              &lt;p className="login-quote-text"&gt;{quotes[currentQuoteIndex]}&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;form onSubmit={handleLogin}&gt;
              &lt;div className="form-group"&gt;
                &lt;label&gt;Username&lt;/label&gt;
                &lt;input type="text" value={username} onChange={(e) =&gt; setUsername(e.target.value)} placeholder="Enter admin username" required /&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div className="form-group"&gt;
                &lt;label&gt;Security Key&lt;/label&gt;
                &lt;input type="password" value={password} onChange={(e) =&gt; setPassword(e.target.value)} placeholder="Enter portal password" required /&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
              {loginError && &lt;p className="form-error"&gt;{loginError}&lt;/p&gt;}
              &lt;button type="submit" className="login-btn"&gt;Initialize Session&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/form&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
}

export default LoginScreen;</pre>

<h3>components/Sidebar.jsx</h3>
<p>The left navigation rail: brand, admin profile, the four tab buttons, and the logout button.</p>
<pre>function Sidebar({ activeTab, setActiveTab, onLogout }) {
  return (
    &lt;aside className="app-sidebar"&gt;
      &lt;div className="sidebar-brand-area"&gt;
        &lt;div className="brand-pulse-icon"&gt;&#129703;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div className="brand-title-text"&gt;HEMO&lt;span className="brand-sub-title"&gt;GRID&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div className="sidebar-admin-profile"&gt;
        &lt;div className="profile-avatar"&gt;AD&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div className="profile-details"&gt;
          &lt;span className="profile-name"&gt;System Admin&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;span className="profile-status"&gt;Online Mode&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;nav className="sidebar-nav-menu"&gt;
        &lt;button className={`nav-menu-item ${activeTab === 'donors' ? 'active' : ''}`} onClick={() =&gt; setActiveTab('donors')}&gt;Donor Registry&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;button className={`nav-menu-item ${activeTab === 'stats' ? 'active' : ''}`} onClick={() =&gt; setActiveTab('stats')}&gt;Statistics Matrix&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;button className={`nav-menu-item ${activeTab === 'audit' ? 'active' : ''}`} onClick={() =&gt; setActiveTab('audit')}&gt;Ledger & Cash Flow&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;button className={`nav-menu-item ${activeTab === 'settings' ? 'active' : ''}`} onClick={() =&gt; setActiveTab('settings')}&gt;Control Settings&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;/nav&gt;
      &lt;div className="sidebar-footer"&gt;
        &lt;button className="sidebar-logout-btn" onClick={onLogout}&gt;Terminate Session&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/aside&gt;
  );
}

export default Sidebar;</pre>

<h3>components/TopHeader.jsx</h3>
<p>The top bar: the sidebar toggle, the current tab's title, and the &ldquo;Onboard New Donor&rdquo; button (donors tab only).</p>
<pre>function TopHeader({ activeTab, sidebarCollapsed, setSidebarCollapsed, onAddDonor }) {
  return (
    &lt;header className="viewport-top-header"&gt;
      &lt;div className="viewport-header-left-group"&gt;
        &lt;button className={`hamburger-menu-toggle ${sidebarCollapsed ? 'is-closed' : 'is-open'}`}
          onClick={() =&gt; setSidebarCollapsed(!sidebarCollapsed)} aria-label="Toggle Sidebar Menu"&gt;
          &lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;h2&gt;
          {activeTab === 'donors' && 'DONOR REGISTRY CONTROL'}
          {activeTab === 'stats' && 'ANALYTICS & DISTRIBUTIONS'}
          {activeTab === 'audit' && 'SYSTEM REVENUE LEDGERS'}
          {activeTab === 'settings' && 'SYSTEM WORKSPACE CONFIGURATIONS'}
        &lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      {activeTab === 'donors' && (
        &lt;button className="top-bar-action-btn" onClick={onAddDonor}&gt;+ Onboard New Donor&lt;/button&gt;
      )}
    &lt;/header&gt;
  );
}

export default TopHeader;</pre>

<h3>components/DonorsTab.jsx</h3>
<p>The donor registry tab: a search bar and the results table with Modify/Purge buttons per row. It is
&ldquo;dumb&rdquo; &mdash; all data and handlers come from App via props.</p>
<pre>function DonorsTab({ selectedGroup, setSelectedGroup, handleSearch, bloodGroups,
  hasSearched, error, loading, donors, openEditModal, handleDeleteDonor }) {
  return (
    &lt;div className="tab-view-container animate-fade-in"&gt;
      &lt;section className="google-search-container"&gt;
        &lt;div className="google-logo"&gt;BLOOD DIRECTORY&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;form onSubmit={handleSearch} className="google-search-bar-form"&gt;
          &lt;select value={selectedGroup} onChange={(e) =&gt; setSelectedGroup(e.target.value)} className="google-select"&gt;
            &lt;option value=""&gt;All Blood Records&lt;/option&gt;
            {bloodGroups.map((group) =&gt; &lt;option key={group} value={group}&gt;{group}&lt;/option&gt;)}
          &lt;/select&gt;
          &lt;button type="submit" className="google-search-btn"&gt;Execute Index Search&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;/form&gt;
      &lt;/section&gt;

      {hasSearched && (
        &lt;main className="dashboard-content"&gt;
          {error && &lt;div className="alert-message error-box"&gt;{error}&lt;/div&gt;}
          {loading && &lt;div className="alert-message loading-box"&gt;Scanning Indexed MySQL Rows...&lt;/div&gt;}
          {!loading && !error && (
            &lt;table className="donor-table"&gt;
              &lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;ID&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Full Name&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Age&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Group&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Gender&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Phone&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Email&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Status&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Operations&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;
              &lt;tbody&gt;
                {donors.length &gt; 0 ? donors.map((donor) =&gt; {
                  const renderGroup = donor.bloodGroup && typeof donor.bloodGroup === 'object'
                    ? donor.bloodGroup.name || donor.bloodGroup.type : donor.bloodGroup;
                  return (
                    &lt;tr key={donor.id}&gt;
                      &lt;td&gt;#{donor.id}&lt;/td&gt;
                      &lt;td&gt;{donor.firstName} {donor.lastName}&lt;/td&gt;
                      &lt;td&gt;{donor.age || '&mdash;'} Yrs&lt;/td&gt;
                      &lt;td&gt;&lt;span className="blood-badge-icon"&gt;{renderGroup || 'N/A'}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
                      &lt;td&gt;{donor.gender}&lt;/td&gt;
                      &lt;td&gt;{donor.phone}&lt;/td&gt;
                      &lt;td&gt;{donor.email}&lt;/td&gt;
                      &lt;td&gt;&lt;span className={`status-badge ${donor.eligibilityStatus?.toLowerCase()}`}&gt;{donor.eligibilityStatus || 'Eligible'}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
                      &lt;td className="action-cell-buttons"&gt;
                        &lt;button className="edit-action-btn" onClick={() =&gt; openEditModal(donor)}&gt;Modify&lt;/button&gt;
                        &lt;button className="delete-action-btn" onClick={() =&gt; handleDeleteDonor(donor.id)}&gt;Purge&lt;/button&gt;
                      &lt;/td&gt;
                    &lt;/tr&gt;
                  );
                }) : (
                  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colSpan="9" className="empty-row"&gt;No active profiles matching query criteria.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                )}
              &lt;/tbody&gt;
            &lt;/table&gt;
          )}
        &lt;/main&gt;
      )}
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
}

export default DonorsTab;</pre>

<h3>components/StatsTab.jsx</h3>
<p>The statistics tab: summary cards (total, eligible, deferred) and a blood-group distribution bar chart.
It derives all its numbers from the <code>donors</code> list it receives.</p>
<pre>function StatsTab({ donors, bloodGroups }) {
  const statsTotalDonors = donors.length;
  const statsEligibleCount = donors.filter(d =&gt; d.eligibilityStatus?.toLowerCase() === 'eligible').length;
  const statsDeferredCount = donors.filter(d =&gt; d.eligibilityStatus?.toLowerCase() === 'deferred').length;

  const groupDistribution = bloodGroups.reduce((acc, group) =&gt; {
    acc[group] = donors.filter(d =&gt; {
      const gText = d.bloodGroup && typeof d.bloodGroup === 'object' ? d.bloodGroup.name : d.bloodGroup;
      return gText === group;
    }).length;
    return acc;
  }, {});
  const maxDistributionValue = Math.max(...Object.values(groupDistribution), 1);

  return (
    &lt;div className="tab-view-container animate-fade-in"&gt;
      &lt;div className="analytics-summary-cards"&gt;
        &lt;div className="stat-card-widget"&gt;&lt;span className="widget-label"&gt;Total Indexed Database Donors&lt;/span&gt;&lt;h3&gt;{statsTotalDonors} Profiles&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div className="stat-card-widget"&gt;&lt;span className="widget-label"&gt;Active Eligible Candidates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;h3&gt;{statsEligibleCount} Users&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div className="stat-card-widget"&gt;&lt;span className="widget-label"&gt;Temporary Medical Deferrals&lt;/span&gt;&lt;h3&gt;{statsDeferredCount} Holds&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div className="chart-analytics-frame-container"&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;BLOOD GROUP DISTRIBUTION COUNTS&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;div className="native-bar-chart-grid"&gt;
          {bloodGroups.map(group =&gt; {
            const count = groupDistribution[group] || 0;
            const percentageHeight = (count / maxDistributionValue) * 100;
            return (
              &lt;div className="chart-column-node" key={group}&gt;
                &lt;div className="chart-bar-value-label"&gt;{count}&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div className="chart-bar-pillar-wrapper"&gt;
                  &lt;div className="chart-pillar-fill" style={{ height: `${Math.max(percentageHeight, 4)}%` }}&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div className="chart-axis-label-node"&gt;{group}&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
            );
          })}
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
}

export default StatsTab;</pre>

<h3>components/LedgerTab.jsx</h3>
<p>The ledger tab: a net-balance card, a sparkline of the running balance, and the full audit table. It walks
the <code>auditLogs</code> oldest-to-newest to build a running balance.</p>
<pre>function LedgerTab({ auditLogs, auditLoading }) {
  let rollingCashBalance = 0;
  const computedCashPoints = [...auditLogs].reverse().map(log =&gt; {
    rollingCashBalance += Number(log.cashFlowAmount || 0);
    return { ...log, rollingBalance: rollingCashBalance };
  });
  const finalNetWorth = rollingCashBalance;
  const maxBalancePeak = Math.max(...computedCashPoints.map(p =&gt; Math.abs(p.rollingBalance)), 1);

  return (
    &lt;div className="tab-view-container animate-fade-in"&gt;
      &lt;div className="financial-metric-sheet-card"&gt;
        &lt;span className="widget-label"&gt;Net System Running Cash Flow Balance&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;h2 className={finalNetWorth &gt;= 0 ? 'cash-positive' : 'cash-negative'}&gt;PKR {finalNetWorth.toLocaleString()}&lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;

      {auditLoading ? (
        &lt;div className="alert-message loading-box"&gt;Interrogating Ledger Buffer Lines...&lt;/div&gt;
      ) : (
        &lt;table className="donor-table"&gt;
          &lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Log ID&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Timestamp&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Operation&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Details&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Classification&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Cash Flow&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;
          &lt;tbody&gt;
            {auditLogs.length &gt; 0 ? auditLogs.map((log) =&gt; (
              &lt;tr key={log.id}&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;00{log.id}&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;{new Date(log.timestamp).toLocaleString()}&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;{log.operation}&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;{log.details}&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;&lt;span className={`type-tag-flag ${log.logType?.toLowerCase()}`}&gt;{log.logType}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;{log.cashFlowAmount &gt; 0 ? `+PKR ${log.cashFlowAmount}` : log.cashFlowAmount &lt; 0 ? `-PKR ${Math.abs(log.cashFlowAmount)}` : '&mdash;'}&lt;/td&gt;
              &lt;/tr&gt;
            )) : (
              &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colSpan="6" className="empty-row"&gt;No system logging history parameters found.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
            )}
          &lt;/tbody&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
      )}
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
}

export default LedgerTab;</pre>

<h3>components/SettingsTab.jsx</h3>
<p>The settings tab: the light/dark theme switch. The theme is owned by App; this component reads <code>theme</code> and calls <code>setTheme</code>.</p>
<pre>function SettingsTab({ theme, setTheme }) {
  return (
    &lt;div className="tab-view-container animate-fade-in"&gt;
      &lt;div className="settings-panel-card"&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;Workspace Personalization&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;div className="theme-toggle-switch-row"&gt;
          &lt;button className={`theme-toggle-btn-option light-opt ${theme === 'light' ? 'selected' : ''}`} onClick={() =&gt; setTheme('light')}&gt;Light Theme&lt;/button&gt;
          &lt;button className={`theme-toggle-btn-option dark-opt ${theme === 'dark' ? 'selected' : ''}`} onClick={() =&gt; setTheme('dark')}&gt;Dark Theme&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
}

export default SettingsTab;</pre>

<h3>components/DonorModal.jsx</h3>
<p>The add/edit dialog. The same form serves both modes; <code>formData</code>/<code>setFormData</code> are the controlled state,
<code>onSubmit</code> sends it to the API, and <code>onClose</code> dismisses the modal.</p>
<pre>function DonorModal({ formMode, formData, setFormData, bloodGroups, onClose, onSubmit }) {
  return (
    &lt;div className="modal-overlay"&gt;
      &lt;div className="modal-card animate-fade-in"&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;{formMode === 'add' ? 'ONBOARD NEW REGISTRATION' : 'REVISE PROFILE METADATA'}&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;form onSubmit={onSubmit}&gt;
          &lt;div className="modal-grid-inputs"&gt;
            &lt;div className="form-group"&gt;&lt;label&gt;First Name&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type="text" value={formData.firstName} onChange={(e) =&gt; setFormData({ ...formData, firstName: e.target.value })} required /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div className="form-group"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Last Name&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type="text" value={formData.lastName} onChange={(e) =&gt; setFormData({ ...formData, lastName: e.target.value })} required /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div className="form-group"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Donor Age&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type="number" min="17" max="80" value={formData.age} onChange={(e) =&gt; setFormData({ ...formData, age: e.target.value })} required /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div className="form-group"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Blood Group&lt;/label&gt;
              &lt;select value={formData.bloodGroup} onChange={(e) =&gt; setFormData({ ...formData, bloodGroup: e.target.value })}&gt;
                {bloodGroups.map(g =&gt; &lt;option key={g} value={g}&gt;{g}&lt;/option&gt;)}
              &lt;/select&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div className="form-group"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Gender&lt;/label&gt;
              &lt;select value={formData.gender} onChange={(e) =&gt; setFormData({ ...formData, gender: e.target.value })}&gt;
                &lt;option&gt;Male&lt;/option&gt;&lt;option&gt;Female&lt;/option&gt;&lt;option&gt;Other&lt;/option&gt;
              &lt;/select&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div className="form-group"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Phone Line&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type="text" value={formData.phone} onChange={(e) =&gt; setFormData({ ...formData, phone: e.target.value })} required /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div className="form-group full-width-input"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Email Address&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type="email" value={formData.email} onChange={(e) =&gt; setFormData({ ...formData, email: e.target.value })} required /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div className="form-group full-width-input"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Eligibility Clearance&lt;/label&gt;
              &lt;select value={formData.eligibilityStatus} onChange={(e) =&gt; setFormData({ ...formData, eligibilityStatus: e.target.value })}&gt;
                &lt;option&gt;Eligible&lt;/option&gt;&lt;option&gt;Deferred&lt;/option&gt;&lt;option&gt;Ineligible&lt;/option&gt;
              &lt;/select&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div className="modal-action-row"&gt;
            &lt;button type="button" className="cancel-modal-btn" onClick={onClose}&gt;Abort&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;button type="submit" className="save-modal-btn"&gt;Commit Package&lt;/button&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/form&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
}

export default DonorModal;</pre>

<h3>components/Footer.jsx</h3>
<p>A static footer with the centre's address and copyright line.</p>
<pre>function Footer() {
  return (
    &lt;footer className="workspace-institutional-footer"&gt;
      &lt;div className="footer-content-divider"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;p className="footer-address-text"&gt;Regional Blood Centre (RBC), Street 5, Sector H-8/4, Islamabad, Pakistan&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p className="footer-copyright-text"&gt;HemoGrid Administrative Infrastructure&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/footer&gt;
  );
}

export default Footer;</pre>

<p><b>Styles note:</b> the visual appearance, including the light/dark theme colour tokens, lives in
<code>src/index.css</code> and <code>src/App.css</code>. These CSS files define variables (e.g. background, text and accent
colours) that switch based on the <code>theme-wrapper</code> class, which is why toggling the theme instantly restyles
the whole app.</p>

<!-- ============================ CHAPTER 7 ============================ -->
<h1 class="pagebreak">Chapter 7 &mdash; How a Request Flows End-to-End</h1>
<p class="chapter-intro">This chapter follows a single action through every layer, tying the previous chapters together.</p>

<p>Example: an admin edits a donor's age and saves.</p>
<ol>
<li>In <b>DonorModal.jsx</b>, the admin changes the age field and clicks &ldquo;Commit Package&rdquo;.</li>
<li><b>App.jsx</b> <code>handleFormSubmit</code> runs and calls <code>API.put('/donors/5', formData)</code>.</li>
<li><b>api.js</b> sends <code>PUT http://localhost:5236/api/donors/5</code> with the form as JSON.</li>
<li><b>Program.cs</b> allows the request through CORS and routes it by verb to <b>DonorUpdateController</b>.</li>
<li>The controller finds the donor via EF Core, uses <b>DonorWriteHelpers</b> to apply the fields and convert age to a birth date, and calls <code>SaveChangesAsync()</code> which issues an <code>UPDATE</code> to <b>MySQL</b>.</li>
<li>It records a &ldquo;PROFILE MODIFICATION&rdquo; line in <b>AuditLedger</b> and returns <code>204 No Content</code>.</li>
<li>Back in App.jsx, <code>handleSearch()</code> and <code>fetchAuditTrail()</code> re-pull fresh data, so the table and ledger update immediately.</li>
</ol>

<!-- ============================ CHAPTER 8 ============================ -->
<h1 class="pagebreak">Chapter 8 &mdash; Running the Application</h1>
<p class="chapter-intro">This chapter lists the commands to build and start both halves of the system.</p>

<h2>8.1 Prerequisites</h2>
<ul>
<li>.NET SDK (8 or 9) installed.</li>
<li>Node.js + npm installed.</li>
<li>MySQL running, with the <code>blood_bank_ms</code> database imported and credentials matching <code>appsettings.json</code>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>8.2 Start the backend</h2>
<pre>cd "C:\Users\While Geek\Documents\Blood bank"
dotnet build BloodBankAPI\BloodBankAPI.csproj
dotnet run   --project BloodBankAPI\BloodBankAPI.csproj
# Look for: Now listening on: http://localhost:5236</pre>

<h2>8.3 Start the frontend</h2>
<pre>cd "C:\Users\While Geek\Documents\Blood bank\blood-bank-ui"
npm install      # first time only
npm run dev
# Open the printed URL (usually http://localhost:5173)</pre>

<h2>8.4 Log in</h2>
<p>Use the admin credentials configured in <code>App.jsx</code> (username <code>admin</code>). You then land on the Donor
Registry, where you can search, add, modify and purge donors, and view Statistics and the Ledger.</p>

<p class="footer">HemoGrid &mdash; Blood Bank Management System &middot; Project Documentation &amp; Complete Code Reference</p>

